The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Wills Lifestyle has said it would increase its presence across India and double its number of outlets to 80 by 2008. ?India?s retail scenario is fast changing. We have to keep pace and plan to double our stores in the next two years,? marketing and retail general manager Atul Chand said. ITC has drawn up plans to reach out to customers even in three-tier and two-tier cities, he added. 

 Nicholas Piramal India Ltd (NPIL) is planning to invest about Rs 250 crore to expand its diagnostic chain, Wellspring, in 75 urban centres across the country in the next two years. The company has opened a Wellspring lab in Delhi. The labs would be equipped to perform over four million pathology tests every year.

 IBM has introduced new software and services to enable customers to take advantage of the growing trend towards service-oriented architecture. 

